docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, April 22 -- The Commerce Department's study of United States trade with the world in 1932, which was sent to the British Embassy at the latter's request today and presumably laid before the economic conferees, showed in detail the extent of the decline in the volume and value of our shipments to principal markets and compared them with figures for the immediate preceding years.
